  "translations": {
    "en": "O people! No one gains even a fraction by his cleverness, and no one loses even a fraction by his foolishness. So the one who knows this and acts accordingly is the most at ease among people in his benefit, and the one who knows this yet abandons it is the most burdened among people in his loss. How often one who is blessed is being gradually lured astray through those blessings, and how often one who appears deceived among the people is actually being cared for.",
